<HL>
   International Managers
   See Sales, Profit Rise,
   D&amp;B Survey Reports
</HL>
<DATE>
05/18/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4
</SO>
<CO>
   LATAM FREST EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- International business leaders expect sales
and profits to rise this quarter, reversing a recent trend of
pessimism, according to Dun &amp; Bradstreet Corp.'s latest
survey of 10,000 executives from 12 countries.
   The prospects were felt to be bleakest in Brazil,
Australia and England; while optimism ran highest in Italy,
Switzerland and West Germany.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The survey, which included the U.S. and Canada, said
expectations for increases in selling prices and unemployment
were unchanged from the first quarter.
</TEXT>
