<IN>
MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)
</IN>
<LP>
   SINGAPORE -- The Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(Asean) wants more trade and investment from Australia,
Acting Foreign Minister Peter Sung said yesterday.
   Trade between Australia and Asean has risen to 6.7 billion
Australian dollars (US$5.1 billion) in 1988-89 against A$2.9
billion in 1980-81.
</LP>
