   However, Australia's trade with the U.S., Japan, Europe,
South Korea, Taiwan, and Hong Kong has grown much more than
with Asean, he said but did not give figures.
   Mr. Sung said, "Asean's exports to Australia have
continuously faced stringent import regulations such as
import licensing; labeling, packing, health, and safety
standards; quarantine restrictions; and antidumping and
countervailing action."
   Singapore, Brunei, Malaysia, Indonesia, the Philippines,
and Thailand are members of Asean.
