<HL>
   State Jobless Claims Rose
   To 353,000 During Week
</HL>
<DATE>
05/18/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A2
</SO>
<CO>
   LABOR
</CO>
<IN>
ECONOMIC NEWS (ECO)
ECONOMIC AND MONETARY INDICATORS (EMI)
</IN>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- Initial claims for regular state
unemployment benefits rose to a seasonally adjusted 353,000
during the week ended May 5 from 349,000 the previous week,
the Labor Department said.
   The number of people receiving regular state benefits in
the week ended April 28 rose to a seasonally adjusted
2,440,000, or 2.3% of those covered by unemployment
insurance, from 2,398,000 the previous week, when the insured
unemployment rate was also 2.3%.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Counting all state and federal benefit programs, the
number of people receiving unemployment benefits during the
week ended April 28 fell to 2,463,000 from 2,492,800 a week
earlier. These figures aren't seasonally adjusted.
</TEXT>
