<LP>
   TV: Maury Povich, the anchor of Fox Broadcasting Co.'s "A
Current Affair" since it began five years ago, will leave the
nightly tabloid broadcast when his contract expires next May.
He will host an afternoon, daily talk show to be produced by
his company, ACA Productions Inc. and distributed by
Paramount Communications Inc., beginning in September 1991.
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   WHO'S NEWS: Raymond H. Godfrey Jr. was named president and
chief operating officer of Management Co. Entertainment Group
Inc., a talent-management and motion-picture concern. He
succeeds Charles J. Weber, who resigned last fall. . . . Time
Warner Enterprises, a unit of Time Warner Inc., made four
appointments: Mark Mitzner, who was executive vice president
and chief financial officer of Warner's Quantum Media Inc.
unit, was named an executive vice president; Mayo S. Stuntz
Jr., formerly president of Quantum Media Television and an
executive vice president of Quantum Media Inc., was named an
executive vice president; and Brian Bedol, who was executive
vice president of QMI Television and vice president of
Quantum Media Inc., and Stanley B. Thomas Jr., who was senior
vice president of affiliate operations for Time Warner's Home
Box Office Inc. unit, both were named senior vice presidents.
</TEXT>
