<LP>
   Hawker Siddeley Group PLC, a British engineering concern,
bought Eaton Technologies of the U.S. for 38 million pounds
($63.8 million), the company said yesterday.
   The purchase of the Michigan-based electric-motors
manufacturer is the first major acquisition made by
London-based Hawker Siddeley on behalf of its International
