the electric-motors division of Electrohome Ltd., a North
American motors manufacturer, and less than 10 million pounds
for Bull Electric Ltd, a U.K. elevator and lift motors maker.
The exact price paid wasn't disclosed.
   A company spokesman said the acquisition of Eaton "adds to
Hawker Siddeley's leading presence in the U.S." in electric
motors.
